RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 13500. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $50,000 FOR TWO YEAR OLDS THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Maidens Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TORTUGA ISLAND hustled to vie for the early lead, gradually angled in on the backstretch, moved clear on the bend, lengthened command under urging upper stretch then continued to open up while ridden out in the late going. RISKY SPIRIT prominent between rivals, found herself in tight quarters while boxed in behind TORTUGA ISLAND midway on the backstretch, jostled with MISS TENA MARIE briefly past the half mile marker, came into the lane just off the inside, edged ahead for second and battled to hold her position in the waning yards. RED MOSCATO also gradually angled in as he raced in the second flight on the backstretch, jostled with MISS TENA MARIE from the half to seven-sixteenths poles, lost ground four wide through the turn, lodged a mild bid to vie for second in the stretch but lacked the needed late kick. MISS TENA MARIE jostled with SUNDAY SPEIGHT nearing the end of the first furlong, was caught in tight quarters leaving the half mile marker, jostled between RISKY SPIRIT and RED MOSCATO until nearing the turn, angled out through the bend and found best stride too late deep stretch. SUNDAY SPEIGHT gradually angled in leaving the chute, jostled briefly with MISS TENA MARIE nearing the end of the first furlong, was squeezed and checked midway on the backstretch and had no late bid. MOCOWBELL was away somewhat slowly and never a factor. SAPPHIRE NIGHTS displayed early speed from inside but began to fade with a quarter mile to go. The rider of MISS TENA MARIE lodged an objection alleging interference from RISKY SPIRIT approaching the turn. After their review, the stewards did not uphold that claim of foul.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARIA'S GIFT in reserve early along the rail, was roused on the second bend, angled to the outside upper stretch, soon dueled for the lead, edged ahead inside the final furlong, drifted out late under left-handed pressure but held sway. CLOSE TO ME prominent just off the inside, went for the lead three wide on the second turn, battled through the stretch, could not stay with MARIA'S GIFT in the late going but proved easily second best. DEAUVILLE MIST vied for the lead outside BOBBIE TOO TOO on the backstretch, was challenged from outside as well on the second bend, fought in the lane but wore down inside the last eighth. GHAALEB'S DREAMS settled outside, picked up her pace after a half mile, progressed just off the rail on the second turn, fanned to path four entering the stretch and lacked a significant response. BOBBIE TOO TOO broke in stride, was hustled clear and to the inside, shared the lead while in hand on the backstretch, retreated a bit on the second bend and gave way along the rail the last furlong. WEEKEND PASS soon trailed, stayed well off the inside nearly all the way and showed little. BEING CREATIVE raced in contention outside DEAUVILLE MIST, began to fade after a half mile, was unresponsive to urging in the lane, eased deep stretch and walked off.

HARPER BRIANA in contention early toward the outside, did not keep up four wide on the turn, angled in some for the stretch run, took over second from between rivals, gradually angled out as SHORT STRAW came out inside the final eighth and narrowly lasted for the place. FANCY HILL helped prompt the early pace, moved clear for second from path three on the bend, floated out further entering the lane then began to wear down. THIS IS ANFIELD showed little. RAIN ATTACK raced in the second flight between horses then began to fade on the turn. COLLIE WRAYS KITTY very green at the start, was always outrun.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ONE WAY HOME rated off the early speed, was let out after a half mile, engaged PRINCE OF MAYHEM from outside approaching the quarter pole, moved clear leaving the second turn then gradually drifted out as he lengthened command the final furlong. PRINCE OF MAYHEM sprinted away from the rest at the start, was challenged on the second bend, no match for ONE WAY HOME when set down for the drive, began to wear down from inside deep stretch but lasted for the place. CHERNYAHOVSKIY settled inside for six furlongs, commenced his bid leaving the second turn, gained third as he gradually angled in the stretch then leveled off in the late going. KEEN RESPONSE hesitated then made a leap from the gate, was settled inside, angled out to commence his bid on the second turn and also rallied belatedly through the stretch. SON OF GRACE hesitated at the break, was void of speed, though urged along, chased from off the rail, lodged his bid just off the inside leaving the second bend, angled out some to stay clear of SON OF GRACE in the stretch and flattened out the final furlong. TROY OUNCE stumbled a few strides from the gate, chased from path three, closed the gap on the top pair on the second turn, drifted out some upper stretch, began to weave from between rivals inside the last furlong, was steadied and finished in hand.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ARGYBARGY BUCK soon had a clear lead just off the rail, was encouraged to keep the advantage when challenged from outside on the backstretch, moved clear again on the second bend, gradually drifted out through the stretch but kept MAPACHE G at bay. MAPACHE G broke somewhat slowly and soon trailed, commenced his bid after a half mile, lost ground circling rivals five wide through the second turn, angled out some as ARGYBARBY BUCK came out with a furlong to go, gradually closed the gap deep stretch but was too late. STORM BORN prominent from the beginning, progressed from outside on the backstretch, was three wide taking the second bend, ran evenly through the stretch but proved easily best of the others. FUTURE VISION was caught five wide on the first turn, came into contention on the backstretch, improved position four wide on the second bend, altered to the inside for a clear path nearing the last furlong then flattened out in the waning yards. TEA AFTER BALLET crowded briefly at the start, was an early factor between rivals, failed to keep up three wide taking the second turn, moved to the outside upper stretch and only passed a few tired ones. MEMPHIS PRAYER chased from outside, advanced two wide on the second bend, also angled out some upper stretch and improved position late between horses without threatening. TENOR vied for the lead between horses on the backstretch, began to yield on the second turn, lugged in upper stretch, altered out from behind FUTURE VISION once inside the last furlong and continued to fade. OPTION was well placed from inside for six furlongs, began to fade leaving the second bend, altered out when TENOR took his path nearing the eighth pole then was steadied behind the latter deep stretch. OKLAHOMA HEAT chased from between rivals, retreated along the rail on the second turn, angled out some upper stretch, was caught in tight quarters between OPTION and MEMPHIS PRAYER after entering the final furlong and steadied behind TENOR shortly after that. RIP IT RYAN was also away slowly and never a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: COMMISSIONER GULCH was bumped and forced into BE MY BESTIE at the break, progressed from outside, was four wide taking the bend, rallied to gain the advantage with seventy yards left then began to draw off. MOON PIES IMAGE bumped with CANDY LOOKER leaving the chute, chased from just off the rail, angled out into the turn, lost ground fanning outside COMMISSIONER GULCH entering the lane, made a strong move the final eighth, was too late but caught STACY ATTACK for second. STACY ATTACK broke on top, set a pressured pace between horses, moved ahead on the bend, stayed just off the inside, lengthened her lead upper stretch but began to wear down in the late going. BIG SALLY pressed the early leader from outside, stayed in path three taking the turn and flattened out the last eighth. BE MY BESTIE bumped at the break, raced in contention just off the inside, had the rail through the bend then began to flatten out for the drive. SHINE DOWN also bumped with CANDY LOOKER leaving the chute then failed to menace in a ground-saving trip. TIME BREAK broke inward, bumping solidly with COMMISSIONER GULCH, was a factor between rivals on the backstretch but faded two wide on the turn. CANDY LOOKER was squeezed between horses briefly leaving the chute, raced in the second flight along the rail on the backstretch but gave way three wide on the bend.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PAPA ROCKET kept close from outside, angled in midway on the backstretch, progressed two wide on the bend, swung out four wide for a clear path entering the lane, rallied and got up in time. MEGAN'S HONOR pressed the early speed from outside, went for the lead four wide on the turn, angled in some leaving the bend, slowly lugged in while he battled under right-handed pressure, moved in beside RACE DRIVER inside the last eighth, edged ahead in the waning yards but was outfinished. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOVE IT BABY shared the early lead outside MYSWEETANNALYZE, was carried out by the latter entering the lane, edged ahead inside the final furlong and narrowly held on. JAMAICAN TRAFFIC moved toward the outside early on, advanced three wide on the turn, lost ground fanning outside MOVE IT BABY into the stretch, rallied the last eighth and just missed. MISS DUTTON prominent running widest, was four wide on the bend, fanned out behind JAMAICAN TRAFFIC entering the lane, steadily angled in for a clear path, was too late along the rail deep stretch but caught MYSWEETANNALYZE for third. MYSWEETANNALYZE shared the lead off the rail but inside MOVE IT BABY, took the rail into the turn, drifted out to path four into the stretch and slowly wore down in the waning yards. TAPICITA chased from inside, lost considerable ground fanning to the middle of the track for the stretch run and rallied belatedly the final furlong. BALI BABY just behind MYSWEETANNALYZE on the backstretch, did not keep up two wide on the turn and had no stretch bid.
